definitions.definition: Agreement of words with one another; concord .
An alphabetical verbal index showing the places in the text of a book where each principal word may be found, with its immediate context in each place.
A list of occurrences of a word or phrase from a corpus , with the immediate context.
The probability that a pair of individuals will both have a certain characteristic ( phenotypic trait) given that one of the pair has the characteristic.

secondary_definitions: ( grammar , obsolete ) Agreement of words with one another; concord .
( chiefly biblical ) An alphabetical verbal index showing the places in the text of a book where each principal word may be found, with its immediate context in each place.
( computational linguistics ) A list of occurrences of a word or phrase from a corpus , with the immediate context.
( genetics ) The probability that a pair of individuals will both have a certain characteristic ( phenotypic trait) given that one of the pair has the characteristic.
